Rating: 3
I added cumin, paprika, coriander, cayenne and saffron - about 1/2 tsp. each. I used chicken broth instead of water and added about 1 tbs. of tomato paste at the onion browning stage. All in all, I felt this ended up a bit oily even though I took most of the oil out of the pot after I browned the chicken. What I did think was lacking was some lemon to brighten the flavor. So, I added in some lemon zest at the end. It helped. I would make this again but I'd thinly slice a whole lemon and add it to the chicken and spice mixture and let it marinade for at least 6 hours along with some cilantro and Italian parsley. There was a terrific recipe in an old Bon Appetit that I use all the time but is not on the website. It's Chicken Tagine with Olives and Lemon from Ziryab restaurant in Paris. It's my go-to recipe for chicken tagine and has lots of lemon to balance the spices. If Bon Appetit would put this up on the website, it would rank no. 1.

