This is a great recipe to use as a jumping off point, but it needs a lot of tweaks. Most tagines I have had are never this sweet. For a more savory but still flavorful tagine I changed a few things. First, I added to the spice mix: Cumin, coriander, paprika, Cayenne, cardamom - Just a half tsp each. Instead of water I used chicken broth (and double the amount the recipe called for). Used boneless skinless chicken thighs to cut down on fat but keep flavor. Added carrots. Simmered for an hour and a half. Completely scrapped the honey and cinnamon stick and just added the apricots right to the chicken. Served over basmati rice. Excellent, with no cloying sweetness from caramelized honey and fruit.

