This was very flavorful and delicious. I have been trying all kinds of variations in Moroccan recipes. We loved this. I would agree that after browning (I used legs and thighs) I would pour off a lot of the fat before adding the onion. I loved how you stewed the apricots in honey and water first before adding to the pot (I used a Dutch oven). I used California apricots, and that was very tasty prepared this way. In other Moroccan dishes such as lamb prepared in a similar manner, one could use this method with the apricots. In other variations after the onion and garlic is sautéed, other ingredients are sometimes added such as chickpeas, tomatoes. The meat could be seasoned ahead of time and refrigerated to marinate if you wished. Either way you prepare this, the basic version of seasoning, browning, sautéing ingredients and then simmering in a liquid is delicious and is fun to experiment with the slight variations I have found in Moroccan tagine recipes.

