Rating: 4
This was my first time cooking in a tagine, and I have to say it was a "wow" dish with incredible flavor. After reading all the reviews I made a few small adjustments. I used boneless, skinless chicken. Chicken on the bone would provide more flavor, but removing the skin reduces the oil that others complained about. I added chicken broth instead of water to the chicken. I did not fry the nuts in oil. I didn't have almonds, so I pan toasted pinenuts. Pan toasting greatly reduces the oil. I chopped the cilantro and parsley and threw it in without the string. Net time I would delay adding the cilantro and parsley until when you add the apricots to keep the greens brighter. The most important change I believe I made was I used California instead of Turkish apricots. To me Turkish apricots are too sweet, while California apricots provide a tart compliment to the honey. I thought the resulting flavors were really great. I will make again. I am wondering about finishing the dish in the oven instead of on the stove and may try that in the future.

